"The highest priority comment is about the **artifact_catalog.html** template, which is currently corrupted and contains invalid, fragmented, and misplaced HTML and template code. This will prevent the Artifact Catalog page from rendering or functioning correctly, breaking the navigation and user experience.

**Issue:**
- The provided `artifact_catalog.html` content is a jumble of incomplete tags, misplaced elements, and invalid syntax.
- It does not define a proper HTML structure, form, table, or buttons as required by the specification.
- This breaks regulation #3 and #4 because the frontend cannot properly link to backend routes or display the artifact catalog page.

**How to fix:**
- Replace the corrupted `artifact_catalog.html` content with a properly structured HTML template that matches the design and elements specified in the requirements.
- The template should include:
  - A container div with ID `artifact-catalog-page`.
  - A search input with ID `search-artifact`.
  - A button with ID `apply-artifact-filter` to submit the search/filter.
  - A table with ID `artifact-table` displaying artifact details (ID, name, period, origin, exhibition, actions).
  - A button with ID `back-to-dashboard` to navigate back to the dashboard.
- Use Flask's `url_for` for navigation URLs to comply with regulation #3.
- Ensure the form method and action correspond to the backend route `/artifact_catalog`.

**Example snippet to replace the corrupted `artifact_catalog.html`:**

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Artifact Catalog</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ url_for('static', filename='css/styles.css') }}">
</head>
<body>
    <div id="artifact-catalog-page">
        <h1>Artifact Catalog</h1>
        <form method="post" action="{{ url_for('artifact_catalog') }}">
            <label for="search-artifact">Search Artifacts by Name or ID:</label>
            <input type="text" id="search-artifact" name="search-artifact" value="{{ search_query }}">
            <button type="submit" id="apply-artifact-filter">Search</button>
        </form>
        <table id="artifact-table" border="1" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>ID</th>
                    <th>Name</th>
                    <th>Period</th>
                    <th>Origin</th>
                    <th>Exhibition</th>
                    <th>Actions</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                {% for artifact in artifacts %}
                <tr>
                    <td>{{ artifact.artifact_id }}</td>
                    <td>{{ artifact.artifact_name }}</td>
                    <td>{{ artifact.period }}</td>
                    <td>{{ artifact.origin }}</td>
                    <td>{{ artifact.exhibition_title }}</td>
                    <td><!-- Actions can be added here if needed --></td>
                </tr>
                {% else %}
                <tr>
                    <td colspan="6">No artifacts found.</td>
                </tr>
                {% endfor %}
            </tbody>
        </table>
        <button id="back-to-dashboard" onclick="location.href='{{ url_for('dashboard') }}'">Back to Dashboard</button>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
```

**Summary:**
- Fixing the `artifact_catalog.html` template is critical to make the Artifact Catalog page operable.
- This fix ensures compliance with regulations #3 and #4 by properly linking frontend elements to backend routes.
- After this fix, test the `/artifact_catalog` route to confirm the page loads and functions as expected.

Please proceed with this correction first before addressing other issues."

